definition.value: A flavin adenine dinucleotide in which the substituent at position 10 of the flavin nucleus is a 5'-adenosyldiphosphoribityl group.
Any 3-oxo steroid that has beta- configuration at position 5.
An inorganic peroxide consisting of two hydroxy groups joined by a covalent oxygen-oxygen single bond.
The 5-phospho derivative of D-arabinose. It is an intermediate in the synthesis of lipopolysaccharides.
